cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks for learning and regression also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the use of bio-inspired vision sensors and the focus on artificial intelligence suggest that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of event cameras and the focus on motion estimation suggest that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
